{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Priyanshu Chatterjee | native_name = | image = Priyanshu Chatterjee.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | birthname = | birth_date = <!--Birthdate must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs. No IMDb. No public records. See WP:BLPPRIVACY--> | birth_place = [[Delhi]], [[India]] | residence = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]] | yearsactive = 2001–present | occupation = {{ubl|Actor|model}} | spouse = [[Malini Sharma]] (1997–2001) }} '''Priyanshu Chatterjee''' is an [[India]]n film actor and former [[Model (profession)|model]] known for his works in [[Bollywood]], and [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengali cinema]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Priyanshu Chatterjee to play a vital role in ‘Hate Story 3’|url = http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/priyanshu-chatterjee-to-play-a-vital-role-in-hate-story-3/|website = The Indian Express|date = 2015-11-03|accessdate = 2015-12-08}}</ref> He made his Hindi film debut in the box-office success ''[[Tum Bin]]'' in 2001. His other recognized work includes ''[[Aapko Pehle Bhi Kahin Dekha Hai]]'', ''[[Dil Ka Rishta]]'', ''[[Pinjar (film)|Pinjar]]'', ''[[Bhootnath]]'' and ''[[Baadshaho]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/a-nice-man-to-know/article785242.ece |title=a nice man to know |publisher=thehindu/ |date= |accessdate=2010-04-10}}</ref>
==Career== Priyanshu Chatterjee started his modelling career working with projects such as Digjam's Print Campaign, [[W.D. & H.O. Wills|Wills Cigarettes]], [[Levi Strauss & Co.|Levi's]] and [[Four Square]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/fitness/charting-his-own-path/article4319801.ece |title=charting his own path |publisher=thehindu/ |date= |accessdate=2013-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/a-nice-man-to-know/article785242.ece |title=a nice man to know |publisher=thehindu/ |date= |accessdate=2010-04-10}}</ref> Following this, he appeared in a [[Udit Narayan]] music video .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2001/07/08/stories/14082183.htm |title=Bollywood stories |publisher=thehindu |date= |accessdate=2001-07-08}}</ref> Chatterjee made his acting debut with ''[[Tum Bin]]'' (2001), a [[romantic drama]]. [[Bollywood Hungama]] while reviewing ''Tum Bin'', wrote of Chatterjee's performance "Priyanshu has the meatier role and he performs it with utmost sincerity."<ref>{{Cite web|title = Tum Bin Review - Bollywood Hungama|url = http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/508505|website = www.bollywoodhungama.com|accessdate = 2015-12-08}}</ref> After the success of ''Tum Bin'', the director of the film, [[Anubhav Sinha]], decided to cast Priyanshu Chatterjee in his next project, which was ''[[Aapko Pehle Bhi Kahin Dekha Hai]]'', co-starring [[Sakshi Shivanand]], [[Om Puri]] and [[Farida Jalal]]. In the same year, he starred in two more films; ''[[Dil Ka Rishta]]'', co-starring [[Aishwarya Rai]] and the other film being ''[[Pinjar (film)|Pinjar]]'', which once again starred [[Sandali Sinha]]. In 2004, he starred in three unsuccessful films; ''[[Woh]]'', ''[[Julie (2004 film)|Julie]]'' and ''[[Madhoshi]]''. In 2008, he got a small role in the multi-starrer ''[[Bhoothnath]]'', where he played the son of Bhoothnath, portrayed by [[Amitabh Bachchan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodwiki.info/page/Priyanshu+Chatterjee |title=Priyanshu Chatterjee - BOLLYWOOD |publisher=Bollywoodwiki.info |date= |accessdate=2012-07-24}}</ref> In 2015, he was seen in a cameo in ''[[Hate Story 3]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Priyanshu Chatterjee to play a vital role in ‘Hate Story 3’|url = http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/priyanshu-chatterjee-to-play-a-vital-role-in-hate-story-3/|website = The Indian Express|date = 2015-11-03|accessdate = 2015-12-08}}</ref>
